author: Reuters
title: DIARY-Emerging Markets Economic Events to Oct 7
text:
Sept 25 (Reuters) -
For other diaries, please see:
Top economic events
Government debt auctions
Political and general news events
Index of all diaries
Guide to economic indicators
** This Diary is filed daily ***
FRIDAY, SEPTEMBER 25 BEIJING - Officials of the National Bureau of Statistics brief reporters on China's economy amid concerns about a sharper slowdown - 0600 GMT. SATURDAY, SEPTEMBER 26 CHISINAU - National Bank of Moldova holds monetary policy meeting. An interest rate decision is expected.
MONDAY, SEPTEMBER 28 MUMBAI - Indian Finance Minister Arun Jaitley will meet the officials of Reserve Bank of India to discuss October-March borrowing calendar. MUMBAI - Indian Finance Minister Arun Jaitley speaks at a ceremony marking the merger between capital markets regulator Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI) and commodities regulator Forward Markets Commission (FMC) - 0345 GMT. MUMBAI - Indian Finance Minister Arun Jaitley speaks at the Indian Banks' Association gathering - 0700 GMT. MAKATI CITY - Central bank of Philippines Deputy Governor Diwa Guinigundo speaks at second ASEAN fixed income summit TUESDAY, SEPTEMBER 29 TOKYO - OECD E-Leaders 2015 (to Sept. 30). OECD Deputy Secretary General Mari Kiviniemi will deliver opening remarks. MUMBAI, India - Reserve Bank of India holds monetary policy meeting, to announce interest rates. MAKATI CITY - Central bank of Philippines Governor Amando Tetangco speaks at joint general assembly of local fixed income, currency and trust market associations - 1030 GMT. WEDNESDAY, SEPTEMBER 30 WASHINGTON - International Monetary Fund Managing Director Christine Lagarde participates in conversation hosted by the Council of Americas on global economic policies and prospects - 1430 GMT. BUCHAREST - Central bank of Romania holds board meeting, to announce interest rates - 0700 GMT. BANGKOK - Central bank of Thailand releases its economic forecast - 0030 GMT. BANGKOK - Central bank of Thailand will publish the minutes of September policy meeting - 0200 GMT.
THURSDAY, OCTOBER 1 PRAGUE - European Central Bank banking supervision chief Daniele Nouy speaks at the ESE Conference 2015 "Financial supervision in Europe - on the right track?" organized by Deutsche Bundesbank in Prague - 1110 GMT.
FRIDAY, OCTOBER 2 PRAGUE - Czech National Bank will publish the minutes of September governing board meeting - 0700 GMT.
MONDAY, OCTOBER 5
MEXICO CITY - Central Bank of Mexico publishes the minutes of September monetary policy meeting - 1400 GMT. WARSAW - National Bank of Poland holds Monetary Policy Council meeting (to Oct. 6)
TUESDAY, OCTOBER 6
LIMA - International Monetary Fund holds press briefing on the World Economic Outlook - 1400 GMT. LIMA - International Monetary Fund/World Bank discussion on "Ensuring Inclusive Development: Good Practices in Promoting Accountability in Latin America" - 1700 GMT. LIMA - International Monetary Fund/World Bank discussion on "Labor Market's Impact from the Slowdown in Latin America" - 1900 GMT. LIMA - International Monetary Fund/World Bank holds Youth Dialogue - 2030 GMT. LIMA - World Bank holds a discussion on Social Inclusion: WikiStage and World Bank Group Lima Special Event - 2200 GMT. Speakers:- World Bank President Jim Yong Kim and World Bank Managing Director Sri Mulyani Indrawati. BUDAPEST - Central Bank of Hungary non-rate-setting meeting. WARSAW - National Bank of Poland announces rate decision - 0930 GMT.
WEDNESDAY, OCTOBER 7
BUDAPEST - Central Bank of Hungary will publish the minutes of September policy meeting - 1200 GMT. LIMA - International Monetary Fund holds press briefing on Global Financial Stability Report - 1400 GMT. LIMA - International Monetary Fund holds a discussion on "Latin America in the Spotlight: Stronger Institutions, Stronger Growth" - 1430 GMT. Speakers:- IMF Deputy Managing Director Carla Grasso and Central Bank of Jamaica Governor Brian Wynter. LIMA - International Monetary Fund/World Bank discussion on "Flagship: Inequality, Opportunity and Prosperity" - 1500 GMT. LIMA - International Monetary Fund holds press briefing on Fiscal Monitor - 1530 GMT. LIMA - International Monetary Fund/World Bank discussion on Ideas for Action: Youth Engagement for Financing the Future of Development - 1600 GMT.
